<i>noun</i>: 힐난 [힐란], 책망 [챙망], 욕 [욕], 나무람 [나무람] <i>verb</i>: 힐난하다 [힐란하다], 책하다 [채카다], 책망하다 [챙망하다] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>힐난 [힐란]</dt><br>
<dd>blame; criticism; reproach</dd><br>
<dd>트집을 잡아 마음이 편하지 않을 정도로 따지고 듦.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of finding fault with someone in such a persistent and argumentative manner that it upsets the person.</dd><br>
<dt>책망 [챙망]</dt><br>
<dd>scold; reproach; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>잘못을 꾸짖거나 나무람.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of scolding or blaming a person for his/her fault.</dd><br>
<dt>욕 [욕]</dt><br>
<dd>1. foul language; abusive language</dd><br>
<dd>남을 무시하거나 비난하는 상스러운 말.</dd><br>
<dd>Vulgar words used to ignore or criticize someone.</dd><br>
<dd>2. reproach; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>잘못을 해서 듣는 꾸지람.</dd><br>
<dd>A scolding that one gets when one makes a mistake.</dd><br>
<dd>3. shame; humiliation</dd><br>
<dd>부끄럽고 치욕스러운 일.</dd><br>
<dd>Something disgraceful and dishonorable.</dd><br>
<dd>4. labor; pains</dd><br>
<dd>(속된 말로) 수고.</dd><br>
<dd>(slang) Trouble.</dd><br>
<dt>나무람 [나무람]</dt><br>
<dd>scolding; reproach; blaming</dd><br>
<dd>잘못을 꾸짖어 잘 알아듣게 말하는 것. 또는 잘못을 꾸짖어 잘 알아듣게 해 주는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of pointing out the fault of someone and advising the person on how to behave better next time, or the remark itself.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>verb</i><br>
<dt>힐난하다 [힐란하다]</dt><br>
<dd>blame; criticize; reproach</dd><br>
<dd>트집을 잡아 마음이 편하지 않을 정도로 따지고 들다.</dd><br>
<dd>To find fault with someone in such a persistent and argumentative manner that it upsets the person.</dd><br>
<dt>책하다 [채카다]</dt><br>
<dd>scold; reproach; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>잘못을 꾸짖거나 나무라다.</dd><br>
<dd>To scold or blame a person for his/her fault.</dd><br>
<dt>책망하다 [챙망하다]</dt><br>
<dd>scold; reproach; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>잘못을 꾸짖거나 나무라다.</dd><br>
<dd>To scold or blame a person for his/her fault.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>